post_text:
NEW DEVICE DISTRIBUTION PLAN - PLEASE READ

At tonight’s Board meeting, we announced an updated plan to distribute devices. Instead of waiting in line, we are asking parents to click the link below to complete a form indicating that your student or students still need a device. The devices will be delivered to the home address indicated on your student’s registration as soon as they are ready. Deliveries will be made using proper social distancing to ensure the safety of our families and our staff. All remaining devices will be delivered using this process. Please do not come to the pickup sites.

As a reminder, students do not need to use a district-owned device. Any device with an Internet connection can be used to access all programs and apps needed for virtual learning. Students who are unable to get a device before school starts tomorrow will not be penalized in any way.

http://tinyurl.com/MISDDeviceRequest

Walnut Creek Dr, Mansfield TX 76063.

shared_text:
Common Ground Mansfield
March 16 at 11:33 PM ·

Thanks to those that dropped off today. It is a great start but we need so much more!!

Help Common Ground Network to provide hundreds of needed supplemental food bags to be given out to children and families in our community in this season of social distancing and Coronavirus concerns. You can help by dropping off food items in front of the Missions Building, Building D at the First Methodist Church Mansfield, 777 N. Walnut Creek Dr. Please place items in the big blue bins, just outside the entry door marked "D-102".

We are especially in need of single-serve entrée items kids can easily open and safely heat, if needed. Microwaveable is good, but please, nothing that requires refrigeration, stovetop or oven. Here are a few examples:
Ramen noodle microwavable cups
Mac n cheese microwavable cups
Tuna (easy open can or foil package)
Chef Boyardee pasta microwavable cups
Cereal
Fruit cups
Breakfast bars

Thank you for responding to this need! It’s only through the generosity of this community that we are able to support the families of MISD together.
text:
For those of you who asked how you can help, Common Ground Mansfield is currently collecting food items to provide food bags for families in the community while schools are closed. View the list below for what is needed. Information about volunteering is available here: https://commongroundmansfield.org/2020/03/15/responding-to-coronavirus-impacting-our-mansfield-community-volunteer-opportunities.

Common Ground Mansfield
March 16 at 11:33 PM ·

Thanks to those that dropped off today. It is a great start but we need so much more!!

Help Common Ground Network to provide hundreds of needed supplemental food bags to be given out to children and families in our community in this season of social distancing and Coronavirus concerns. You can help by dropping off food items in front of the Missions Building, Building D at the First Methodist Church Mansfield, 777 N. Walnut Creek Dr. Please place items in the big blue bins, just outside the entry door marked "D-102".

We are especially in need of single-serve entrée items kids can easily open and safely heat, if needed. Microwaveable is good, but please, nothing that requires refrigeration, stovetop or oven. Here are a few examples:
Ramen noodle microwavable cups
Mac n cheese microwavable cups
Tuna (easy open can or foil package)
Chef Boyardee pasta microwavable cups
Cereal
Fruit cups
Breakfast bars

Thank you for responding to this need! It’s only through the generosity of this community that we are able to support the families of MISD together.

post_text: Our Ben Barber Innovation Academy students received a game-changing educational tool. Take a look at the school's new Anatomage Table, which will help students visualize anatomy in 3D. The device was sponsored by the Methodist Mansfield Medical Center.
shared_text:
Mansfield ISD Education Foundation is at Ben Barber and Frontier High School.
February 19 at 1:34 PM · Mansfield, TX ·

It’s hard to pronounce, but it’s a game-changer in the way it brings anatomy to life! “Anatomage “ is what’s new at Mansfield ISD!

Thanks to a $75,000 Health Science grant through the Education Foundation in partnership with Methodist Mansfield Medical Center, students at Ben Barber get life-like cadaver experiences through the new Anatomage Table!

We appreciate our community partners like Methodist Mansfield Medical Center that support public education at Mansfield ISD!
Methodist Mansfield Medical Center

post_text: Well that was fun! Thank you to everyone who came and supported a great cause that will help make the holidays brighter for children. You can take a look at some of the MISD Toys for Tots pictures here: https://mansfieldisdpics.smugmug.com/EVENTS/CommunityEvents/Toys-for-Tots/2019-MISD-Toys-for-Tots/. (We'll add more as we get them.) Good night!
